# Task S55-T7: Reports and Lists

## Description
1. Reports are wide 99% of the time. Ensure a reliable and easily discoverable horizontal scroll mechanism for data tables in the Reports tab.
2. Add a "Download to File" button(s) (e.g., CSV, PDF, Excel) for generated reports.
3. Clarify logic when switching to the List view: should the List cover the entire screen or an expanding portion? Implement a standard behavior where the list provides maximum readability.
4. If a report fails to build, render an Error Screen that natively includes a "Restart" or "Retry" button.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Reports can be panned horizontally without breaking the main layout window.
- Error states don't leave the user dead-ended; they can hit Restart.
- Table export actions are clearly visible.
